<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: DIAZ LAKE A WORTHWHILE SIERRA STOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Eastern Sierra trout season has been closed for more than six weeks, but 
some might find a trip to Diaz Lake worthwhile. 
</P>
<P>
 One of only a few year-round fisheries in the region, Diaz Lake, off Highway 
395 east of Lone Pine, will receive a bonus plant of 500 two-pound rainbow 
trout that had been used as brood stock at the Department of Fish and Game's 
Hot Creek Hatchery in Mammoth Lakes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
