<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Walt Disney Co. Eyes Latin Sites: The company is considering building a theme 
park somewhere in South America early in the next decade, a company executive 
said."If we open a park in Latin America, it won't be in this decade but in the 
year 2000 and something," Stephen de Kanter, executive vice president for Latin 
America of Disney Consumer Products, said at a news conference. The park would 
be built in Argentina, Bolivia, Chile, Uruguay, Paraguay or Peru, he said. 
</P>
