<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Van Nuys High has hired Mark Pomerantz as the school's football coach, 
replacing George Engbrecht, who resigned Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Pomerantz, 39, has been an assistant at Van Nuys the past three years. 
Engbrecht is leaving the campus to accept a job at Hoover High as an assistant 
principal. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack Molina, assistant principal at Van Nuys, said that Engbrecht's letter of 
recommendation was a strong factor in the selection of Pomerantz. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys finished 6-5, losing to Venice in the first round of the City Section 
3-A Division playoffs. Van Nuys advanced to the playoffs three consecutive 
years under Engbrecht. 
</P>
