<P>
IRVINE HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL BOOSTER LYLE PHELPS DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lyle Phelps, the father of two Irvine High quarterbacks, Mike and Ryan Phelps, 
died at home Monday of colon cancer. He was 56. 
</P>
<P>
 Phelps, who followed Irvine football for more than 20 years, was profiled Oct. 
18 by The Times after the Vaqueros' 9-7 loss to Newport Harbor in the Sea View 
League opener. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Coach Terry Henigan started junior backup Ryan Phelps for the first 
series of downs in that game to allow Lyle the opportunity to hear his son's 
name announced as a starter. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to his wife, Carol, and Ryan and Mike, Irvine's all-time passing 
leader who is a redshirt freshman at Oregon, Lyle Phelps is survived by 
daughters Becky and Wendy, and a son from his first marriage, Bob, of Tustin. 
MARTIN HENDERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
