<P>
FORMER USC PLAYER JAILED IN ASSAULTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG SANDOVAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael O'Brien, a walk-on football player earlier this season at USC, is 
expected to be arraigned today for allegedly assaulting three students on 
campus. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Brien, 22, surrendered to police Tuesday.He has been accused of punching a 
female student in the face and breaking the jaw and eye socket of a male 
student on Sept. 16. On Dec. 5, O'Brien allegedly broke a male student's leg 
and ankle by throwing him to the ground. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Brien, who left the team in October according to a USC spokesperson, is 
being held on $120,000 bail and if convicted of the three counts of assault 
could be sentenced to 11 years in state prison. 
</P>
<P>
 A senior, O'Brien did not play in any games for the Trojans this season. GREG 
SANDOVAL 
