<HEADLINE>
<P>
5 SENTENCED IN FATAL CHINA FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Chinese court sentenced five people, including two firefighters and a Hong 
Kong businessman, to prison Tuesday in connection with a toy factory fire a 
year ago that killed 87 workers. 
</P>
<P>
 The November, 1993, blaze at the Zhili Handicraft Factory was the third in 
four months in or near Shenzhen, a Chinese boom town bordering Hong Kong, 
pointing to neglect of industrial safety as China rushes for economic growth. 
</P>
<P>
 The sentences ranged from two to 17 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
