<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: NORTH; BREA; FORUM TO EXAMINE FUTURE OF LIBRARIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Librarians, city officials and business operators are holding a public forum 
Jan. 12 to explore ways to finance new libraries and make existing libraries 
more self-sufficient in response to declines in funding. 
</P>
<P>
 State Librarian Kevin Starr will provide an overview of the future, current 
entrepreneurial library experiments and today's social and economic problems 
facing libraries. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Forum for Entrepreneurial Libraries" will take place at the Embassy 
Suites Hotel, 900 E. Birch St., from 8:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Ideas to be discussed will include using libraries in shopping centers and 
offering conference areas, business services and determining how libraries can 
capitalize on urban redevelopment. 
</P>
<P>
 A library technology exhibit will be displayed and brainstorming sessions will 
take place as well. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, a case study on how a San Francisco library generated $30 million 
through philanthropy will be presented. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsors of the event predict the demise of libraries without creative 
innovations to generate operating funds to save them. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is open to the public. Cost to register is $35 before Dec. 30 and 
$50 after that date. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 863-9200.MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
