<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY LOOKING FOR TOP DECORATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents who spot a particularly clever holiday decoration should immediately 
inform the authorities. 
</P>
<P>
 The Beautification-Environmental Commission is seeking nominations for the 
1994 holiday awards program by Tuesday to honor decorations that are 
"attractive, well-built and demonstrate pride in the community," said Patty 
Kryger of the Public Works Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The creations can be on private dwellings or multi-tenant and commercial 
buildings, and the commission will judge a separate category for "special 
recognition." 
</P>
<P>
 Winners will receive a certificate of recognition and a dinner for two from 
the City Council in January. 
</P>
<P>
 Nominations should be sent to Kryger at the Buena Park Public Works 
Department, P.O. Box 5009, Buena Park, Calif. 90622. Nominators may also call 
(714) 562-3651. 
</P>
<P>
 They should note the name, address, telephone and nearest cross street of the 
decoration. 
</P>
