<P>
BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wordcraft Systems Acquisition: Wordcraft Systems Inc. said Tuesday that it has 
agreed to acquire its United Kingdom licensor and business partner, Wordcraft 
International Ltd., for $3.1 million in cash and stock.The Irvine maker of 
computer software for automated office equipment said it expects to complete 
the acquisition Feb. 28. The company said Wordcraft International, a designer, 
manufacturer and distributor of PC-fax software systems, will have sales in 
excess of $1.2 million in 1994, mostly royalties, and projected sales of $4 
million in 1995. Wordcraft Systems said it expects its consolidated sales for 
1995 to total $12 million. 
</P>
