<HEADLINE>
<P>
WASTE MANAGEMENT FIRM SAYS SEC REPORTS WILL BE FILED LATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Security Environmental Systems Inc. said Tuesday it does not expect to file 
its most recent annual and quarterly reports with the Securities and Exchange 
Commission until early in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 The company also said it will report a "sizable loss" for the fiscal year 
ended June 30 as well as a loss for the first quarter of its current fiscal 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 In a press release, the Huntington Beach-based company tied the reporting 
delay to an ongoing review by its independent auditors. 
</P>
<P>
 Security Environmental also announced several management changes. Jess Turner 
was appointed chairman, succeeding Alfred Grossman, who was removed as chairman 
of the board on Oct. 10. John Wheeler, chief operating officer, was also 
appointed to the board. Ellen L. Batzel was appointed chief executive officer 
of the company. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are working with our auditors to locate and supply information and 
documentation," Batzel said. 
</P>
<P>
 Security Environmental, founded in 1972, offers waste management, remediation 
and transportation services to government and industrial generators of waste. 
GREG JOHNSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
