<P>
CIMCO INC. REPORTS LOSS OF $542,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cimco Inc., a Costa Mesa manufacturer of plastic components for commercial, 
industrial and medical markets reported a loss of $542,000, or 18 cents a 
share, for its second fiscal quarter ended Oct. 31.That contrasted with a 
profit of $27,000, or 1 cent a share, for the same period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Sales rose 9% to $20.3 million from $18.6 million. For the first half of its 
fiscal year, the company posted a loss of $1.1 million, or 37 cents a share, 
contrasted with profit of $134,000, or 5 cents a share, for the same period a 
year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 Six-month sales were up 2% to $38.5 million from $37.9 million, the company 
said. 
