<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH; LAKE FOREST; ROAD CLOSED AFTER 
CRASH SPILLS CHEMICALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two people suffered minor injuries in a collision that caused 20 gallons of 
swimming pool chemicals to spill on El Toro Road and shut down traffic for 
about an hour Tuesday morning, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 A pickup truck driven by Sang You, 34, and a car driven by Juan 
Vargas-Palomeque, 25, collided at Aliso Park Drive and El Toro Road about 7:20 
a.m., Sheriff's Lt. Bill Leonard said. 
</P>
<P>
 You was carrying the pool chemicals in the back of his pickup. 
</P>
<P>
 Leonard said one of the drivers ran a red light but it hadn't been determined 
whether it was You or Vargas-Palomeque. 
</P>
<P>
 County Fire Department spokeswoman Kathleen Cha said four gallons of muriatic 
acid and 16 gallons of chlorine were spilled in the accident. 
</P>
<P>
 When mixed, the two chemicals produced toxic vapors that can be "a real 
powerful respiratory irritant," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Muriatic acid, a common industrial cleaning agent, can cause irritation to the 
eyes and skin. 
</P>
<P>
 The county's hazardous materials unit and firefighters used soda ash to 
neutralize the acid and washed it down with water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
