<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: CENTRAL; TUSTIN; SUGGESTIONS SOUGHT FOR NAME OF SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is one name-calling event that people can enjoy. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tustin Unified School District wants the public to submit names for the 
first elementary school in Tustin Ranch.The school at Robinson and Keller 
streets will open in the fall of 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 Suggested names may include a street name, a tree, an event, a housing 
development, the school's location, something that reflects the state's Spanish 
influence or that has a scholastic reference. The names of persons are 
acceptable if the nominee is dead and had been someone with an education, 
public service or humanitarian background. 
</P>
<P>
 A typewritten justification, not to exceed two pages, must be submitted with 
the nomination. The deadline is Jan. 13. Send entries to the superintendent's 
office, 300 S. C St., Tustin, Calif. 92680. For more information, call (714) 
730-7305.BERT ELJERA 
